INSERT INTO `blogentries` 
(`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)
INSERT INTO `blogentries` (`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)VALUES
( 1, 2, 'normal', 'TODAY ON FRANKLY SPEAKING - YOUR LIFE''S WORK; A MASTERPIECE', '<p>If you sincerely open your eyes and look around, if you refuse to let your subjective mindset and restricting thinking cover your true sight, you&rsquo;ll realize more than ever before in history, this millennium offers the greatest opportunities to achieve whatever you want to achieve and be the best you can ever be in life.</p>\r\n<p>Today, we have no more barriers and restriction in business and social communication globally, information on any subject matter is just a click away, opportunities abound across markets, across nations, across the globe, individual liberty has become more popular and indeed we are enjoying an era of free enterprise.</p>\r\n<p>Success, freedom, happiness and financial independence has never been more accessible anytime else in history than now!&nbsp;</p>', '<p>If you sincerely open your eyes and look around, if you refuse to let your subjective mindset and restricting thinking cover your true sight, you&rsquo;ll realize more than ever before in history, this millennium offers the greatest opportunities to achieve whatever you want to achieve and be the best you can ever be in life.</p>\r\n<p>Today, we have no more barriers and restriction in business and social communication globally, information on any subject matter is just a click away, opportunities abound across markets, across nations, across the globe, individual liberty has become more popular and indeed we are enjoying an era of free enterprise.</p>\r\n<p>Success, freedom, happiness and financial independence has never been more accessible anytime else in history than now!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>There have never been more billionaires in history as now and we&rsquo;ve never had so many children and teenage millionaires in history as now! Many people with ideas, creativity, positive thinking, solutions and tenacity are becoming millionaires overnight. In this season you could be broke today and become a multi-millionaire the next day! It&rsquo;s a season of unprecedented prosperity and great wealth!</p>\r\n<p>Unfortunately, many of us today suffer from money worries more than any other kind of worry. Hanker and desperation for money by many stems from its lack, and has pushed people into all kinds of atrocities and illegalities because they are unaware of the modern ways to wealth.</p>\r\n<p>Those that don&rsquo;t have and don&rsquo;t want ill-gotten wealth have however remained poor and continue to endure a life of hardship and lack because; they are ignorant about the real modern ways to wealth.</p>\r\n<p>Truth is, the frustration and the terrible implication of not knowing how to access money has made some people perceive riches as bad and rich people as evil and selfish.</p>\r\n<p>But may I say to you this morning that irrespective of your perception and opinion, money makes people happy; money can facilitate better relationships, better families and good quality life.</p>\r\n<p>Money grants you access to the best things life has to offer. Money may not be the absolute key to happiness but having money makes you happy. You have better homes, afford better quality education, live in better neighborhoods, enjoy better health care, put on better clothing and enjoy respect and relevance everywhere you go. Poverty makes you unhappy, unpopular, disdained, disrespected, misused and abused.</p>\r\n<p>My purpose this morning is not to promote materialism or ostentatious living, I just want you to move up to that level where you can afford a good life, free from fear, insecurity and deprivation.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;I believe there are just some things you should just be able to afford in life, when you can&rsquo;t afford the basic necessities in life, it means you are poor.</p>\r\n<p>Affordable in my opinion should be how you should approach material acquisition in life, not the expensive or cheap approach. Cheap or expensive is an illusion, it only applies to the intending buyer; it is not of general market application. What you call cheap may be expensive to someone else. A fifty thousand naira mobile phone may be quite cheap for some people, they won&rsquo;t even bother buying it because it&rsquo;s too cheap and wouldn&rsquo;t suit their status, and some other person would save so much money for a long time to buy a twenty thousand naira phone. Cheap or expensive is exclusive to the purse or pocket of the buyer.</p>\r\n<p>But when you begin to think from the perspective of affordability, it&rsquo;s a thinking and a view that is progressive by nature, affordability simply means for now I can&rsquo;t buy it because I don&rsquo;t have enough now, but as soon as I have enough, I will buy it.</p>\r\n<p>This sets you on a progressive track towards better living standards in life. It delivers you from a mentality of poverty. A mindset of poverty holds a permanent opinion about expensive and cheap irrespective of how much they have in their pockets. Hence, they will never want to buy the best because to them it is expensive even if they can afford it.</p>\r\n<p>Dear friends, I want you to stop and think for a moment, what is your own definition of success? What does success mean to you? You see success is a relative term because we differ in our goals, dreams and expectations in life, but today I just want you to think again about what that point of success would be for you.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Becoming the managing director? Owning your own multi-million dollar business? Building your own house, building an estate?</p>\r\n<p>For me success is when I&rsquo;m numbered amongst the top five public speakers in the world; then I&rsquo;ll know I&rsquo;m successful. What is success for you, I&rsquo;m sure it&rsquo;s obviously different from mine, and you can see also it&rsquo;s not really about money.</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;d like you to do something today, go back in time in your life to maybe when you were fifteen or sixteen; based on what you know now, what choices and decisions would you rather have made in life? What different choices would you have made? What mistakes would you have avoided, what counsel and popular opinion would you have disregarded?</p>\r\n<p>Would you be in the industry you&rsquo;re currently in, would you have studied the course you studied in school, would you have married the person you married, would you have birthed the number of kids you have?</p>\r\n<p>I mean these are personal questions and only you can answer them personally and sincerely, I know for some of us having our spouses by our sides right now we would say yes to the question about whom you&rsquo;re married to, but the real answer remains true only in your mind, it is that personal.</p>\r\n<p>I have good news for you today, it doesn&rsquo;t matter where you&rsquo;re at right now, you can start right now to begin to take deliberate steps towards your success definition.</p>\r\n<p>Revisit your dreams of yesteryears and reawaken them, shut your mind to the popular declarations of hardship, lack, poverty and deprivation, these are not of global application, open your mind and see beyond your location, don&rsquo;t have a local and restricted dream and vision, to be truly rich in this world the whole world must be your market. Hey! It&rsquo;s accessible now through technology, you can do business globally now without leaving your house! Open your eyes, open your mind, don&rsquo;t allow infrastructural challenges, inflation and exchange rate make things look impossible. See a global picture and set your success dream on high, above nations and continents; never stay local.</p>\r\n<p>If you can start all over again what will your success journey be like?</p>\r\n<p>Dear friend, you can&rsquo;t hit a target you can&rsquo;t see. You must have a mental picture of what your ideal life and success and accomplishment would look like. This picture will protect you from a life of mediocrity and the temptation to settle for less.</p>\r\n<p>Make a master piece of your life&rsquo;s work, dream and ambition, remember you&rsquo;re older now than you were last night; we only live once. Take the chance.</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy your day.</p>', 
INSERT INTO `blogentries` (`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)VALUES( 1, 1, 'normal', '6 PHRASES YOU SHOULD NEVER USE AT THE OFFICE', '<p><span lang="EN-US">The corporate world is increasingly sieving out every form of ethical informality.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>Listed below are my top six suggestions for the &ldquo;<strong>DO NOT SAY</strong>&rdquo; list. Using these comments in business (and life) can diminish your stature in the eyes of others, minimize what you are saying, or tarnish your professional image</p>', '<p><span lang="EN-US">The corporate world is increasingly sieving out every form of ethical informality.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="EN-US">Listed below are my top six suggestions for the &ldquo;<strong>DO NOT SAY</strong>&rdquo; list. Using these comments in business (and life) can diminish your stature in the eyes of others, minimize what you are saying, or tarnish your professional image:</span></p>\r\n<p><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US">&Oslash;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US">Can I ask a question?</span></strong><span lang="EN-US"><br /> </span><span lang="EN-US">You don&rsquo;t have to ask permission; just ask the question.</span></p>\r\n<p><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US">&Oslash;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US">I&rsquo;m sorry to bother you.</span></strong><span lang="EN-US"><br /> </span><span lang="EN-US">Why are you a bother? You can say, &ldquo;Excuse me. Do you have a moment?&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US">&Oslash;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US">I was hoping that you could spare a few moments.</span></strong><span lang="EN-US"><br /> </span><span lang="EN-US">Same as above. Simply say, &ldquo;Excuse me. Do you have a moment?&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US">&Oslash;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN-US">&middot;<strong>Thank you for listening to me.</strong></span><span lang="EN-US"><br /> </span><span lang="EN-US">At the end of a presentation, you should say, &ldquo;Thank you.&rdquo; This lets the audience know that the presentation is over. You don&rsquo;t have to thank people for listening to you. Aren&rsquo;t your comments and opinions worthwhile?</span></p>\r\n<p><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US">&Oslash;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US">I will be honest with you.</span></strong><strong><span lang="EN-US"><br /> </span></strong><span lang="EN-US">Aren&rsquo;t you always honest? You don&rsquo;t need to use this phrase.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>I was just wondering if perhaps.</strong><br /> This phrase is a passive way of asking a question or backing into a statement. You can eliminate &ldquo;I was just wondering if perhaps&rdquo; and simply ask a question or make a statement. Instead of &ldquo;I was just wondering if perhaps there will be enough computers for the project?&rdquo; you can say, &ldquo;Will there be enough computers for the project?&rdquo;</p>', '22, January 2014 04:21:07', '', '', 20493, 32, 0, '6-PHRASES-YOU-SHOULD-NEVER-USE-AT-THE-OFFICE', 'no', 'no', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, 'active');
INSERT INTO `blogentries` (`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)VALUES( 1, 2, 'normal', 'REAL ESTATE BUSINESS SET TO BOOM IN KENYA!', '<p>Are you looking for where to invest in 2014?</p>\r\n<p>The Kenyan Government has, once again, reiterated its readiness to partner with the private sector in order to construct and sell houses.</p>\r\n<p>In Kenya, there has been a robust growth in housing development in the last five years. Nonetheless, there remains a very high and unmet demand - particularly in the urban areas across the country which shelters over 1.8million visitors annually!</p>\r\n<p>Under the Vision 2030, a target of over 200,000 housing units per year is required.</p>\r\n<p>As such, the government is ready to work out modalities of partnering with private sector to construct and sell houses, including low cost houses to Kenyans.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&lsquo;Safari land&rsquo; calls.</p>\r\n<p>This might just be your chance to strike gold!</p>', '<p>Are you looking for where to invest in 2014?</p>\r\n<p>The Kenyan Government has, once again, reiterated its readiness to partner with the private sector in order to construct and sell houses.</p>\r\n<p>In Kenya, there has been a robust growth in housing development in the last five years. Nonetheless, there remains a very high and unmet demand - particularly in the urban areas across the country which shelters over 1.8million visitors annually!</p>\r\n<p>Under the Vision 2030, a target of over 200,000 housing units per year is required.</p>\r\n<p>As such, the government is ready to work out modalities of partnering with private sector to construct and sell houses, including low cost houses to Kenyans.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&lsquo;Safari land&rsquo; calls.</p>\r\n<p>This might just be your chance to strike gold!</p>', '22, January 2014 04:46:39', '22, January 2014 04:51:01', 'Wed, 22 Jan 2014 04:51:01 +0100', 1702, 33, 0, 'REAL-ESTATE-BUSINESS-SET-TO-BOOM-IN-KENYA', 'no', 'no', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, 'active');
INSERT INTO `blogentries` (`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)VALUES( 1, 1, 'normal', 'TODAY ON FRANKLY SPEAKING - THE CORE OF THE MATTER.', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Many businesses today are under tremendous pressure and anxiety about where their growth will come from this year. Teams are meeting, putting together plans and strategies for success. Competitors are also planning on how they can take on a larger share of the market; deliver more in volume, revenue and profit.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The dynamism and inconsistencies in the market and business environment keep making it difficult for business leaders to chest-beat about good profit at the end of the financial year. The quality, commitment and passion of employees also put a question mark on the likelihood of fully implementing strategy and delivering the expected results.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;Truth is, many people today are just going to work, doing their best and hoping for the best. Very few are actually confident about success at the end of the period.</p>', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Many businesses today are under tremendous pressure and anxiety about where their growth will come from this year. Teams are meeting, putting together plans and strategies for success. Competitors are also planning on how they can take on a larger share of the market; deliver more in volume, revenue and profit.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The dynamism and inconsistencies in the market and business environment keep making it difficult for business leaders to chest-beat about good profit at the end of the financial year. The quality, commitment and passion of employees also put a question mark on the likelihood of fully implementing strategy and delivering the expected results.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;Truth is, many people today are just going to work, doing their best and hoping for the best. Very few are actually confident about success at the end of the period.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">With the continuous growth in knowledge and capacities for business management and professional business practice, it is quite popular today to declare the customer as king. Marketers are quick to refer to the customer as king and as far as business success is concerned, efficient customer service is a very critical key to delivering the numbers.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Company-wide marketing orientation is also a popular advocacy with serious minded businesses nowadays. And this philosophy supports the prioritizing of the customer as the most important element in business practice; in fact without the customer, the business dies.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">But overtime it&rsquo;s amazing how this business fact has lost its realism as it were - becoming a philosophy mouthed, advocated but denied in practice hence, no real impact and consequently no expected results.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">As a customer I have severally been exposed to sales people and customer service personnel who make attempts at satisfying me and at the end of the day just end up irritating me.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">It&rsquo;s amazing how so many businesses today underrate and take for granted the intelligence of their customers.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Customer service ought to have the true ability to service the customer and satisfy the customer. Customer service is not just a set of activities wired into the process of making a sale, giving it a robust appearance but lacking in essence and the real ability to make customers happy.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Customer service is not supposed to be packaged in a way to insult the intelligence of the customer or compensate for product failure. Customer satisfaction should actually have the ability to satisfy the need and expectations of the customer.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Many marketers and sales team very much know their customer service and satisfaction packages won&rsquo;t work because it&rsquo;s actually cost led not purpose driven, it&rsquo;s also put in place as palliatives when the product or service fails to satisfy the customer, so they just do it for the sake of doing it; they know it will not make customers happy or satisfied. If the customer is truly the king, customer service shouldn&rsquo;t be compensating for product failure; it should actually be put in place to make sure the product or service satisfies the customer &ndash; the king.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In my submission, many businesses today are busy mocking, disrespecting and upsetting their customers; the king, because they are desperately pursuing profit, hence their customer service approach is purposed to compensate for their diminishing quality of product or insensitive price increases. This style can never sustain customer growth and loyalty, subsequently, with time customers would move.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In my opinion, I think a business organization consist of a group of persons brought together for the common purpose of creating and keeping customers.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">I believe the primary responsibility of any organization is to create, grow and retain as many customers as possible, unfortunately, many organizations, out of desperation for profit sacrifice the source of revenue and profit; the customer.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Respecting a king goes far beyond bowing to the king and saying nice things and praising the king. Real respect for a king is in listening to the king and meeting his needs.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Every now and again I see many businesses miss out on this profound fact and gradually tow the path of subsequent decline and liquidation.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Immediately businesses sense a threat of an impending shortfall in expected revenue or profit, the first to feel the heat is the customer, how? Companies begin to compromise on quality and at times quantity and size of their products. If it&rsquo;s a tangible product, the size may reduce or the quality of ingredients compromised. If companies don&rsquo;t touch the product, they alternatively jack up the price.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The customer is most of the time the first victim when a business appears to be struggling. Where then does the marketing philosophy of customer being king apply?</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Dear friends, I believe what we see expressed at the level of organizations is a reflection of the thinking and the judgments of individuals team members.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Our collective reasoning, analyses and conclusions are what you find our organizations implementing.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">So much like the business, as individuals we have in and around our lives some individuals that are very close and useful, these are people who in time past believed in us, supported us, encouraged us and stood by us when it was as though we were struggling with our careers, capacities and general approval by the business. They supplied our emotional, psychological and competence needs at the work place.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">These people believed in us and saw what many others in the organizations didn&rsquo;t see, we enjoyed their protection, training and motivation and with time we were able to overcome our limitations, struggles and suddenly became super stars.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Suddenly everyone began to see our potentials, gifts, capacities and abilities and we became a major part of the business and we became more relevant and even became involved in decision making.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We became the favorite of the company leadership and the leadership had our ears, what you say to the leaders, they believe and your counsel is quite valuable to them. Gradually you become more powerful, influential and strong within the business and you begin to rise.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Being comfortable with this new status of power, relevance and general acceptance, we become very protective of it and would do anything to remain trusted, relevant and powerful within the system.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Unfortunately, if in the process of time that high and powerful position you occupy is suddenly threatened by situations and circumstances within the system or your personal ambition and profiting begins to drive you, the very persons or people that gave you the opportunity for ascension are the very first ones you deal with and hurt to secure your position or that promotion.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Those you once respected, revered and treated as king then become the very first you scheme, plot and strategize to sideline or even send packing in order to achieve your own ambition.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">What you fail to see or acknowledge is the fact that these same people who supported and helped you up can as well bring you down effortlessly by withdrawing their support, patronage and backing.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">No individual can stand alone and survive alone. And be sure those that groomed you and saw you rise know you better than your newly found allies and close supporters, hence, they know your weaknesses and know just where and how to get you.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Dear friend, loneliness at the top comes when you discard and do away with those who were there with you and supported you when you were still ascending. Just like the very first customers of a business are very important to any business.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Lack of confidence and insecurity is the only motivation for sidelining friends and contemporaries when eventually you feel you&rsquo;re at your top or achieved something worthwhile.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The fact that they know you in and out makes you uncomfortable hence you&rsquo;ll rather draw close to those who don&rsquo;t really know you and can&rsquo;t demystify you, don&rsquo;t you realize true help comes from people who can truly tell you the truth because the truly know you?</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Many businesses die today because they keep treating their loyal customers wrong when they experience a revenue or profitability threat by compromising quality or increasing prices. Eventually these customers who were there to support and grow the business from the start become disgruntled and disappointed and consequently withdraw their patronage and support for the business.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">What many businesses still fail to embrace is the fact that business survival and growth is about creating, retaining and growing customers not making profit. You can never be profitable without customers; chasing profit at the expense of your customer defiles logic and will kill your business faster than anything else.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Chasing your career goals and ambition at the expense of those who raised and trained you, will frustrate you and make you very lonely and overwhelmed at the end of the day and consequently you wouldn&rsquo;t last that long in that top position or office.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Dear friends, respect the customer, respect the king, respect those who make you, don&rsquo;t use or abuse your support, protect and preserve them, they will protect and preserve you in return.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;Enjoy your day.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>CONNECT WITH US ON SOCIAL MEDIA!</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Twitter:</strong>&nbsp;@franklyafolabi or&nbsp;<strong>Click</strong>&nbsp;<a href="http://www.twitter.com/franklyafolabi">http://www.twitter.com/franklyafolabi</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Facebook fan page</strong>:&nbsp;<strong>Click to Like</strong>&nbsp;<a href="http://www.facebook.com/franklyspeakingwithmuyiwaafolabi">http://www.facebook.com/franklyspeakingwithmuyiwaafolabi</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Google Plus</strong>: Muyiwa Afolabi</p>', '22, January 2014 05:07:24', '22, January 2014 05:12:20', 'Wed, 22 Jan 2014 05:09:03 +0100', 468, 34, 0, 'TODAY-ON-FRANKLY-SPEAKING--THE-CORE-OF-THE-MATTER', 'no', 'no', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, 'active');
INSERT INTO `blogentries` (`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)VALUES( 1, 1, 'normal', 'The best way to run your business meeting in 2014 revealed!', '<p>In this super-fast age of ours, good meeting etiquette is a necessity if any business must come good.</p>\r\n<p>Quite often, organizations hold meetings within which strategies and business ideas are analyzed. But all too often, <a href="http://www.entrepreneur.com/topic/meetings">meetings</a> run longer than necessary and consequently fail to keep attendees engaged.</p>\r\n<p>Whether you''re meeting with partners, vendors or employees, showcase your boardroom brilliance with these meeting musts:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>&nbsp; <strong>Determine the objectives.</strong> A clear goal will set the tone for the meeting and determine its direction. Your goal should be specific and measurable. If you''re expecting attendees to brainstorm, ask each participant to arrive with a list of ideas.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>&nbsp; <strong>Ask yourself if a meeting is actually necessary.</strong> Meetings can be expensive. To calculate the precise cost, multiply the hourly wage of each person present by the length of the gathering. If your objective can be met through e-mail, conference call, Skype, or even a quick one-on-one discussion, skip the meeting altogether.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>In this super-fast age of ours, good meeting etiquette is a necessity if any business must come good.</p>\r\n<p>Quite often, organizations hold meetings within which strategies and business ideas are analyzed. But all too often, <a href="http://www.entrepreneur.com/topic/meetings">meetings</a> run longer than necessary and consequently fail to keep attendees engaged.</p>\r\n<p>Whether you''re meeting with partners, vendors or employees, showcase your boardroom brilliance with these meeting musts:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp; <strong>Determine the objectives.</strong> A clear goal will set the tone for the meeting and determine its direction. Your goal should be specific and measurable. If you''re expecting attendees to brainstorm, ask each participant to arrive with a list of ideas.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<ul style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<li><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp; <strong>Ask yourself if a meeting is actually necessary.</strong> Meetings can be expensive. To calculate the precise cost, multiply the hourly wage of each person present by the length of the gathering. If your objective can be met through e-mail, conference call, Skype, or even a quick one-on-one discussion, skip the meeting altogether.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<ul style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<li><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp; <strong>Invite decision-makers.</strong> The most effective meetings involve stakeholders to ensure decisions can be made immediately. If a key decision-maker is unavailable, ask a subordinate to attend. Ideally, this person will be able to speak for their supervisor, and--at the very least--take notes and report back.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp; <strong>Stand up.</strong> Routine meetings designed to touch base with employees and discuss status reports can usually be accomplished in 15 minutes or less. You''ll be more likely to keep the meeting short and to the point if everyone remains standing.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<ul style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<li><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp; <strong>Schedule strategically.</strong> If you want each meeting participant to be fully engaged, avoid Monday mornings, when everyone is catching up on e-mail. Also avoid Friday afternoons, when employees are busy wrapping up the week and looking forward to the weekend. Schedule meetings on a day and time when participants are most likely to engage.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<ul style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<li><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp; <strong>Set a time limit and stick to it. </strong>Meetings that drag on for hours cause attendees to lose patience and focus. Attention spans are short, and time is valuable. The most productive meetings start on time and end on time.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<ul style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<li><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp; <strong>Prioritize the agenda. </strong>Don''t leave the most important topics for last. To ensure that the highest priority objectives are met, discuss the most pertinent issues first. That way, if someone needs to step away or leave the meeting early, you''ll still have accomplished your main goals.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<ul style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<li><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp; <strong>Stick to the agenda. </strong>The agenda is an outline--a framework--to keep everyone on topic and to maintain the meeting''s flow. The agenda should be kept to one page and should not include anything other than main topics of conversation. Sidebar conversations waste valuable time. If participants insist on talking out of turn, step in and suggest that they talk after the meeting or schedule a separate discussion. Then segue immediately back to the topic at hand.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<ul style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<li><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp; <strong>Deliver concepts through stories. </strong>When you present a group with key concepts or new ideas, especially models that are difficult to understand, explain why they should care. Frame the issue with a quick story and use examples.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp; <strong>Wrap it up clearly. </strong>At the end of the meeting, quickly reiterate any decisions, deadlines, and clarify any follow-up action required. All meeting participants should understand exactly what is expected of them. Schedule any follow-up meetings immediately</span></li>\r\n</ul>', '22, January 2014 05:23:43', '22, January 2014 10:52:56', 'Wed, 22 Jan 2014 05:28:44 +0100', 1839, 35, 0, 'The-best-way-to-run-your-business-meeting-in-2014-revealed', 'no', 'no', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, 'active');
INSERT INTO `blogentries` (`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)VALUES( 1, 1, 'normal', 'HAVE YOU BEEN TO THE NIGERIAN THEATRE OF DREAMS?', '<p>To every Nigerian, especially those who live in the nation&rsquo;s commercial capital city (Lagos), the National Arts Theatre in Iganmu is a national edifice that will always be pretty to behold.</p>\r\n<p>Below are some&nbsp;facts about&nbsp;the National Arts Theatre:</p>\r\n<p>Built in 1976, the national arts theatre hosted the world acclaimed festival of arts and culture(FESTAC) in 1977.</p>\r\n<p>Located in Iganmu, Lagos, it was built during the military regime of OLUSEGUN OBASANJO.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;A major attraction in Lagos, the national theatre boasts of a main auditorium that can seat 3,000 people as well as a conference hall with 1,000 seater capacity.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Added to these, it also has<strong>&nbsp;</strong>2 Cinema Halls (350 seats capacity each), a lobby with 250 seats and an exhibition hall that can seat 1,500 people. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A language translation facility that feeds you with 8 different versions of whatever is said.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>To every Nigerian, especially those who live in the nation&rsquo;s commercial capital city (Lagos), the National Arts Theatre in Iganmu is a national edifice that will always be pretty to behold.</p>\r\n<p>Below are some&nbsp;facts about&nbsp;the National Arts Theatre:</p>\r\n<p>Built in 1976, the national arts theatre hosted the world acclaimed festival of arts and culture(FESTAC) in 1977.</p>\r\n<p>Located in Iganmu, Lagos, it was built during the military regime of OLUSEGUN OBASANJO.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;A major attraction in Lagos, the national theatre boasts of a main auditorium that can seat 3,000 people as well as a conference hall with 1,000 seater capacity.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Added to these, it also has 2 Cinema Halls (350 seats capacity each), a lobby with 250 seats and an exhibition hall that can seat 1,500 people.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>A language translation facility that feeds you with 8 different versions of whatever is said.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/national theatre 1.jpg" alt="National Arts Theatre" width="288" height="206" />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<img src="../media/multimedia/national theatre 2.jpg" alt="National Arts Theatre1" width="305" height="206" />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img src="../media/multimedia/national theatre 3.jpg" alt="National Arts Theatre 2" width="248" height="204" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '22, January 2014 07:09:42', '09, July 2014 12:11:07', 'Wed, 09 Jul 2014 12:11:07 +0100', 763, 36, 0, 'HAVE-YOU-BEEN-TO-THE-NIGERIAN-THEATRE-OF-DREAMS', 'no', 'no', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, 'inactive');
INSERT INTO `blogentries` (`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)VALUES( 1, 1, 'normal', 'NOEL JONES', '<p>Wise, dedicated orator and philosopher Bishop Noel Jones uniquely promotes reconciliation and redemption; the pastor of the City of Refuge Church (in Gardena, California), he has strengthened and encouraged faith across the globe, from England to Jamaica to Africa.<br /> <br /> Bishop Jones maintains an active speaking schedule around the U.S. and the world. His ministry&rsquo;s primary focus is spreading the gospel of Jesus Christ through the Word via media resources</p>\r\n<p><strong>Early life</strong>Jones was born in Spanish Town, Jamaica on January 31, 1950. One of seven children born to Bishop Robert (who was a politician and Apostolic clergyman) and Marjorie Jones. He was raised alongside a diverse array of siblings (one of whom is the actress and singer <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grace_Jones">Grace Jones</a>. His parents took him and his two siblings at the time, Chris and Grace, and relocated to Syracuse, New York in 1965.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Wise, dedicated orator and philosopher Bishop Noel Jones uniquely promotes reconciliation and redemption; the pastor of the City of Refuge Church (in Gardena, California), he has strengthened and encouraged faith across the globe, from England to Jamaica to Africa.<br /> <br /> Bishop Jones maintains an active speaking schedule around the U.S. and the world. His ministry&rsquo;s primary focus is spreading the gospel of Jesus Christ through the Word via media resources.</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/noel jones 2.jpg" alt="" width="381" height="280" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Early life</strong>Jones was born in Spanish Town, Jamaica on January 31, 1950. One of seven children born to Bishop Robert (who was a politician and Apostolic clergyman) and Marjorie Jones. He was raised alongside a diverse array of siblings (one of whom is the actress and singer <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grace_Jones">Grace Jones</a>. His parents took him and his two siblings at the time, Chris and Grace, and relocated to Syracuse, New York in 1965.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/noel jones 3.jpg" alt="noel jones" width="528" height="224" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>Early education and ministry</strong></p>\r\n<p>Jones received the call to ministry at the age of nineteen. He attended St. Jago High School and went on to attain a Bachelor of Science in Theology degree from <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Aenon_Bible_College&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1">Aenon Bible College</a>. He would go on later to receive his doctorate from the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Circle_of_Faith">International Circle of Faith</a>. At the age of twenty-six, he accepted his first pastorate at Bethel Temple of Longview in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Longview,_Texas">Longview, Texas</a>.</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/noel jones 4_1.jpg" alt="noel jones 1" width="483" height="272" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Current ministry</strong></p>\r\n<p>In June 1994, Jones was chosen to succeed Bishop Robert W. McMurray as pastor to approximately 1,000 members of the Greater Bethany Community Church, located at 84th Hoover Street, Los Angeles, California. During his tenure, the membership of the church has increased so significantly that, in 2003, a new building was acquired in Gardena, California. The new sanctuary, now known as "The City of Refuge", accommodates a growing membership of 17,000. The church has a choir known as the City of Refuge Sanctuary Choir. Their 2007 debut album,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>Welcome to the City</em>, charted on the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Billboard_200">Billboard 200</a> chart and made number one on the Billboard Top Gospel Albums chart.</p>', '22, January 2014 07:24:17', '23, February 2016 15:06:34', 'Wed, 22 Jan 2014 10:14:36 +0100', 977, 37, 0, 'NOEL-JONES', 'no', 'no', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, 'inactive');
INSERT INTO `blogentries` (`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)VALUES( 1, 1, 'normal', ' Jonathan Set To Retain Oduah', '<p>With the submission of 12 ministerial nominees to the Senate for screening on Tuesday by President Goodluck Jonathan, there are indications that Stella Oduah, the controversial Minister of Aviation, may retain her position in the Federal Executive Council, contrary to the expectations of most Nigerians.</p>\r\n<p>It was gathered that apart from his conviction that the minister is doing a good job in the aviation sector, the President has also come under tremendous pressure from leading Igbo groups and personalities who argued that Oduah is being unduly persecuted.</p>\r\n<p>There have been agitations for the sack of Oduah over the series of scandals that have dogged her tenure as a minister. There was a general uproar last year when information emerged that the Nigeria Civil Aviation Authority, NCAA a parastatal under the Aviation Ministry bought two armoured BMW cars for at the price of N255 million.</p>\r\n<p>Joe Obi, a media aide to the Minister initially told the media that the cars were bought for the Minister because there were threats to her life as a result of the various reforms she has been implementing in the Aviation sector. But the Minister later denied this as she insisted that the vehicles were for the operations of the NCAA.</p>\r\n<p>But after a public hearing into the controversies, the House of Representatives Committee on Aviation indicted the Minister over the purchase of the cars.</p>\r\n<p>Fellow Nigerians, whats your take on this?</p>', '<p>With the submission of 12 ministerial nominees to the Senate for screening on Tuesday by President Goodluck Jonathan, there are indications that Stella Oduah, the controversial Minister of Aviation, may retain her position in the Federal Executive Council, contrary to the expectations of most Nigerians.</p>\r\n<p>It was gathered that apart from his conviction that the minister is doing a good job in the aviation sector, the President has also come under tremendous pressure from leading Igbo groups and personalities who argued that Oduah is being unduly persecuted.</p>\r\n<p>There have been agitations for the sack of Oduah over the series of scandals that have dogged her tenure as a minister. There was a general uproar last year when information emerged that the Nigeria Civil Aviation Authority, NCAA a parastatal under the Aviation Ministry bought two armoured BMW cars for at the price of N255 million.</p>\r\n<p>Joe Obi, a media aide to the Minister initially told the media that the cars were bought for the Minister because there were threats to her life as a result of the various reforms she has been implementing in the Aviation sector. But the Minister later denied this as she insisted that the vehicles were for the operations of the NCAA.</p>\r\n<p>But after a public hearing into the controversies, the House of Representatives Committee on Aviation indicted the Minister over the purchase of the cars.</p>\r\n<p>Fellow Nigerians, whats your take on this?</p>', '22, January 2014 11:43:04', '09, July 2014 11:56:14', 'Wed, 09 Jul 2014 11:56:14 +0100', 294, 67, 0, '-Jonathan-Set-To-Retain-Oduah', 'no', 'no', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, 'inactive');
INSERT INTO `blogentries` (`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)VALUES( 1, 1, 'normal', 'BEHOLD ZUNGERU...THE PLACE WHERE NIGERIA WAS BORN', '<p>For a long part of my life, I have always wondered why Lord Frederick Lugard amalgamated the Northern and Southern protectorates into what became Nigeria, immediately the people shouted &ldquo;<em>happy new year</em>&rdquo; in 1914. Even if he had signed, couldn&rsquo;t his secretary and the man whose name gave us Port-Harcourt, Lord Harcourt have read out something else?&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Why did his queen, Flora Shaw, give us the name Nigeria; a name that sourced from the phrase <em>Niger &ndash;area</em>?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Had she given us a name like <strong><em>Slaveria</em></strong>---probably from the combination of the words &lsquo;<strong><em>slave</em></strong> and <strong><em>area</em></strong>&rsquo;, would our fathers have done anything?</p>\r\n<p>There must have been something wonderful about the people of the community where this whole thing happened.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><img src="../media/multimedia/zungeru.jpg" alt="z" width="297" height="250" />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<img src="../media/multimedia/zungeru....old.jpg" alt="old" width="324" height="250" />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<img src="../media/multimedia/zungerru...2007 (2).jpg" alt="new" width="343" height="246" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/lord luggard 2.jpg" alt="lord lugard" width="218" height="275" /></p>\r\n<p>For a long time, I have always wondered why Lord Frederick Lugard amalgamated the Northern and Southern protectorates into what became <em><strong>Nigeria</strong></em>, immediately the people shouted &ldquo;<em>happy new year</em>&rdquo; in 1914. Even if he had signed, couldn&rsquo;t his secretary and the man whose name gave us Port-Harcourt, Lord Harcourt have read out something else?&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Why did his queen, Flora Shaw, give us the name Nigeria; a name that sourced from the phrase <em>Niger &ndash;area</em>?</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/flora shaw.jpg" alt="Flora Shaw" width="170" height="220" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Had she given us a name like <strong><em>Slaveria</em></strong>---probably from the combination of the words &lsquo;<strong><em>slave</em></strong> and <strong><em>area</em></strong>&rsquo;, would our fathers have done anything?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Zungeru, a town in Niger State was where it all began. The small town was exactly where the inspiration behind the country Nigeria came down.&nbsp;Subject to popular belief, the name came alive when some whites saw a native playing an instrument called &lsquo;DUNGURU&rsquo;. When asked to pronounce the name of the instrument, all they could manage was a battered remix and ever since, that has remained the name of the town.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;The capital of the Northern Protectorate from 1902 to 1916, many of us hardly knew that Zungeru was the father of Kaduna, Lagos and Abuja when it comes to being the national sit of power.&nbsp; .</p>\r\n<p>Zungeru was established by the Lord Fredrick Luggard in 1900 as a military and administrative settlement, with the aim of protecting the colonized area of the country from the then Northern invaders. The first organized military &ldquo;<strong>The West Africa Frontier Force</strong>&rdquo; which later changed to the present day &ldquo;Nigerian Army&rdquo; was setup in Zungeru</p>\r\n<p>Zungeru was Lord Lugard''s operational base until the capital of the North was shifted to the new town of Kaduna 1916 just before the end of the First World War. The Lugard cemetery lies on a hill just outside the town. It&rsquo;s a beautiful place to be buried, apology to the truth that the dead lay thousands of miles from home.</p>\r\n<p>The popular Zungeru Cemetery hosts the remains of some colonial masters who died in the struggle of colonization and pacification. To many Nigerians, the ancient town is noted as the abode of power as railway workers were known to have played significant roles in the political developments of the nation.</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/zungerus railway club.jpg" alt="Railway Club" width="373" height="219" /></p>\r\n<p>Owing to this splendid truth, it wouldn&rsquo;t be out of place to say that the vision of a &lsquo;<strong><em>free Nigeria&rsquo;</em></strong> was first conceived in this place. As a matter of fact, Zungeru is home to the first indigenous Governor General of Nigeria, Dr. Nnamdi Azikwe, who was born in Zungeru in 1904. Late Chief Odumegwu Ojukwu; the Ikemba of Nnewi was also born in Zungeru in November, 1933. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/zik and the family.jpg" alt="zik and family" width="269" height="281" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I would have loved to know the house of Ikemba&rsquo;s father. Sir Louis Odumegwu Ojukwu was indeed a parcel of brilliance. None, to me, but a diligent man goes on to become the founding father of the Nigerian Stock Exchange.</p>\r\n<p>However, it is only painful to note that the residence of the parents of these two great Nigerians have now been leveled. One can only manage to locate the sites.</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/download (1)_1.jpg" alt="Ojukwu Odumegwu" width="255" height="290" /></p>\r\n<p>Laid at this cemetery, among others, is the founder of the Boy Scout Movement, Sir Henry James Speed. At the part section of Black men Cemetery lays the remains of Nigerians (Blacks) who died during the colonial administration in Zungeru.</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/download (12).jpg" alt="Zungeru Cemetry" width="299" height="198" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Thanks to its proximity to Abuja, the federal capital territory, Zungeru is accessible to the whole of Nigeria and can be reached by the world at large. Considering the fact that it is strategically placed, its historical strength can be logically harnessed to promote the needed bond that has once and should always unite Nigerians across barriers.</p>\r\n<p>Perhaps you want a live amalgamation feed from a man who witnessed the birth of Nigeria as a fifteen year old, Zungeru currently boast of Alhaji Salihu Gomna now striding up to 115years of age.</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/download (21).jpg" alt="Alhaji Gomna" width="291" height="234" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; Find below the relics of the famous Ebenezer Anglican church, where Zik was dedicated.</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/ebenezer cathedral.png" alt="Anglican Cathedral" width="294" height="229" /></p>\r\n<p>The miracle you&rsquo;ve been waiting to see may just happen if you endeavour to worship alone in the 1903 model Ebenezer Anglican church---the place where Dr Nnamdi Azikwe was baptized. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Zungeru town, as well as the military cemetery, is a blessing to every generation that will ever be born&nbsp;in Nigeria.</p>\r\n<p>Who knows if this relic of colonial life, the last of many, is the place in which you must worship in order to become the next Nigerian president?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '22, January 2014 08:08:20', '22, January 2014 12:02:35', 'Wed, 22 Jan 2014 08:09:17 +0100', 129, 38, 0, 'BEHOLD-ZUNGERU...THE-PLACE-WHERE-NIGERIA-WAS-BORN', 'no', 'no', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, 'inactive');
INSERT INTO `blogentries` (`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)VALUES( 2, 1, 'normal', 'NIGERIA; THIS IS RESPECT!', '<p><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_detailpage&amp;v=YT5m9Fn9RBg">http://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_detailpage&amp;v=YT5m9Fn9RBg</a></p>\r\n<p>Hello Nigerians,</p>\r\n<p>There was a time we were as a nation respected everywhere in the world!&nbsp;We had very intelligent, confident and proud leaders who as ''youths'' made great impact globally.</p>\r\n<p>Can we possibly regain this respect? &nbsp;Kindly&nbsp;click on the link above and watch the&nbsp;video of our former&nbsp;Prime&nbsp;Minister''s visit to the&nbsp;United&nbsp;States of&nbsp;America in the 60s'' and please share your views.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you</p>', '<p><img src="../media/multimedia/images.jpg" alt="tafawa balewa" width="367" height="386" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_detailpage&amp;v=YT5m9Fn9RBg">http://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_detailpage&amp;v=YT5m9Fn9RBg</a></p>\r\n<p>Hello Nigerians,</p>\r\n<p>There was a time we were as a nation respected everywhere in the world!&nbsp;We had very intelligent, confident and proud leaders who as ''youths'' made great impact globally.</p>\r\n<p>Can we possibly regain this respect? &nbsp;Kindly&nbsp;click on the link above and watch the video of our former&nbsp;Prime Minister''s visit to the United States of America in the 60s'' and please share your views.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you</p>', '22, January 2014 08:39:32', '09, July 2014 10:54:06', 'Wed, 09 Jul 2014 10:54:06 +0100', 337, 41, 0, 'NIGERIA-THIS-IS-RESPECT', 'no', 'no', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, 'inactive');
INSERT INTO `blogentries` (`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)VALUES( 2, 2, 'normal', 'WHAT DO YOU SEE?', '<p>Fellow&nbsp;Nigerians,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>What do you see?</p>\r\n<p>What''s your dream?</p>\r\n<p>What''s your contribution?</p>\r\n<p>Let''s make it happen!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>IT''S POSSIBLE!</p>', '<p><img src="../media/multimedia/images (12).jpg" alt="lagos" width="540" height="494" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Fellow Nigerians,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>What do you see?</p>\r\n<p>What''s your dream?</p>\r\n<p>What''s your contribution?</p>\r\n<p>Let''s make it happen!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>IT''S POSSIBLE!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '22, January 2014 09:00:50', '09, July 2014 11:13:27', 'Wed, 09 Jul 2014 11:13:27 +0100', 354, 42, 0, 'WHAT-DO-YOU-SEE', 'no', 'no', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, 'inactive');
INSERT INTO `blogentries` (`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)VALUES( 2, 1, 'normal', 'TYE TRIBBET', '<p>Tribbett was raised in a Pentecostal Apostolic church in Camden, New Jersey. His father is a pastor and his mother is a minister well &nbsp;known as a &nbsp;disc jockey in the Philadelphia area. He is married to Shant&eacute; Tribbett, who was a member of Greater Anointing, and they have two daughters together. He also has a brother, Thaddaeus, who is part of the band ''Soundcheck'' and is now the current bassist for artist Estelle. Tye also has two sisters; one sister, DeMaris, also sang in Greater Anointing.</p>\r\n<p>Change is not an event, it&rsquo;s a process. And for Tye Tribbett &mdash; husband, father of two, Gospel singer, songwriter, producer, preacher and business man &ndash; the pruning process of change and deliverance took root after an intense period of turmoil. Touching many with his musical ministry, Tye&rsquo;s fourth album release Fresh, on Axis Music Group/Columbia, positions him to step forth boldly with a new message of grace after weathering the storm of change in his personal life and ministry. &ldquo;Fresh means restored, new creature and it&rsquo;s my announcement that nothing is the same,&rdquo; Tye declares, &ldquo;my thinking, my business, my patterns, everything is new.&rdquo;</p>', '<p><strong>Personal life</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tribbett was raised in a Pentecostal Apostolic church in Camden, New Jersey. His father is a pastor and his mother is a minister well &nbsp;known as a &nbsp;disc jockey in the Philadelphia area. He is married to Shant&eacute; Tribbett, who was a member of Greater Anointing, and they have two daughters together. He also has a brother, Thaddaeus, who is part of the band ''Soundcheck'' and is now the current bassist for artist Estelle. Tye also has two sisters; one sister, DeMaris, also sang in Greater Anointing.</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/tye tribett 1.jpg" alt="tye" width="382" height="164" /></p>\r\n<p>Change is not an event, it&rsquo;s a process. And for Tye Tribbett &mdash; husband, father of two, Gospel singer, songwriter, producer, preacher and business man &ndash; the pruning process of change and deliverance took root after an intense period of turmoil. Touching many with his musical ministry, Tye&rsquo;s fourth album release Fresh, on Axis Music Group/Columbia, positions him to step forth boldly with a new message of grace after weathering the storm of change in his personal life and ministry. &ldquo;Fresh means restored, new creature and it&rsquo;s my announcement that nothing is the same,&rdquo; Tye declares, &ldquo;my thinking, my business, my patterns, everything is new.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/tye tribet 003.jpg" alt="tye1" width="466" height="302" /></p>\r\n<p><span lang="EN-GB">Tye has been making bold declarations and bringing forth change within his music for years with Tye Tribbett &amp; Greater Anointing (&ldquo;G.A.&rdquo;), his family and ministry. Together they toured and performed with some of the biggest artists in the secular world including Whitney Houston, Faith Hill and Tim McGraw, Luther Vandross, Elton John, Justin Timberlake and Jill Scott to name a few. It was during a consecration period in between their first two albums Life (2004) and Victory Live! (2006), where Tye &amp; G.A. made the decision to focus solely on gospel.<br /></span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="EN-GB"><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="../media/multimedia/tye tribett 3.jpg" alt="tye 2" width="496" height="306" /></span></p>\r\n<p>The success of Life was bolstered to the Billboard Top 10 Gospel Album chart with the infectious singles &ldquo;No Way&rdquo; and &ldquo;Everything.&rdquo; Victory Live! entered the Billboard Top Gospel Album chart at #1, generated the #1 Gospel Radio single, &ldquo;Victory,&rdquo; and earned Tribbett two Stellar Award wins and three Grammy nominations &mdash; Best Gospel Performance (&ldquo;Victory&rdquo;); Best Gospel Song (&ldquo;Victory&rdquo;); and Best Contemporary R&amp;B Gospel Album. With his third installment Stand Out (2008) entering the Billboard Gospel chart at #1, Tye further propelled the goodness of God with his musical message.</p>\r\n<p><span lang="EN-GB"><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="../media/multimedia/tye tribet 4.jpg" alt="tye4" width="380" height="380" /></span></p>\r\n<p>It was within the last year, however, that Tye learned much more about God&rsquo;s goodness and grace while dealing with the issue of infidelity in his marriage. Tye moved through a dark period that led to thoughts of suicide. It was here when he acknowledged he moved far away from his foundation. Ironically it was sixty day sabbatical from his musical ministry that realigned Tye to focus on his personal ministry with God and his family first. Tye recalls, &ldquo;I turned away from God and as soon as I turned back around He was ready to receive me, and I learned God does not hold grudges at all.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="EN-GB"><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="../media/multimedia/tye tribet 005_1.jpg" alt="tyue" width="347" height="297" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>On the fiftieth day, Tye received a revelation in Isaiah 43:18-19 &ldquo;Forget the former things; do not dwell on the past. See, I am doing a new thing!&rdquo; The revelation and acceptance opened Tye&rsquo;s eyes and behold, God set forth the next phase of change. &ldquo;The Lord restored [my marriage] for the gospels&rsquo; sake, not the gossip&rsquo;s sake.&rdquo; The process also consisted of transition with Greater Anointing. &ldquo;There is a season for everything and no matter how great a season is, the next one is always coming. There was nothing wrong with G.A., it was just time for another season,&rdquo; proclaims Tye. &ldquo;I had to release everybody to be who they were called to be.&rdquo; Tye was clear that the Lord restored his marriage to a new position and with obedience and renewed sensibility, his music would also be restored.&nbsp;</p>', '22, January 2014 09:21:16', '23, February 2016 15:04:57', 'Wed, 22 Jan 2014 09:28:20 +0100', 4883, 43, 0, 'TYE-TRIBBET', 'no', 'no', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, 'inactive');
INSERT INTO `blogentries` (`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)VALUES( 2, 2, 'normal', '13 SHOCKING FACTS ABOUT NIGERIA.', '<p>Nigeria is home to seven percent (7%) of the total languages spoken on earth. Taraba state alone has more languages than 30 African countries combined. The importance of this fact is appreciated when one understands that language is the &ldquo;soul of culture&rdquo; (as Ngugi wa Thiongo famously said). Without language, there will be nothing to call proverbs, riddles, stories and other aspects of culture that give us identity. UNESCO puts forward that languages represent an extraordinary wealth of creativity, linguistic diversity that &nbsp;correlates with cultural diversity. This means Nigeria can look inwards and drive itself to become the greatest hub for cultural tourism on earth, and consequently empower its citizens tremendously in the process. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Nigeria is home to seven percent (7%) of the total languages spoken on earth. Taraba state alone has more languages than 30 African countries combined. The importance of this fact is appreciated when one understands that language is the &ldquo;soul of culture&rdquo; (as Ngugi wa Thiongo famously said). Without language, there will be nothing to call proverbs, riddles, stories and other aspects of culture that give us identity. UNESCO puts forward that languages represent an extraordinary wealth of creativity, linguistic diversity &nbsp;that correlates with cultural diversity. This means Nigeria can look inwards and drive itself to become the greatest hub for cultural tourism on earth, and consequently empower its citizens tremendously in the process. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/taraba state.png" alt="taraba" width="304" height="304" /></p>\r\n<p>The Walls of Benin (800-1400AD), in present day Edo State, are the longest ancient earthworks in the world, and probably the largest man-made structure on earth. They enclose 6,500 square kilometers of community lands that connect about 500 communities. At over 16,000km long, it was thought to be twice the length of the Great Wall of China, until it was announced in 2012 (after five years of meticulous measurement by some Chinese surveyors) that the Great Wall is about 21,000km long. This however failed to rule out the fact that the wall of Benin is longer because the length of natural barriers like mountains and rivers were added to the resultant measurement of the Chinese wall. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/walls of benin.jpg" alt="benin" width="298" height="228" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;In another celestial and marvelous twist, the Yoruba tribe-- of course in Nigeria, has the highest rate of twin births in the world. <em><strong>Igbo-Ora</strong>,</em> a little town in Oyo state, has been nicknamed'' Twin capital of the World'' thanks to its unusually high rate of twin birth--- as high as 158 twins per 1000 births. According to a YouTube video, Titi (a white lady who speaks Yoruba), and which was centered on twin births in Igbo-Ora, one of the locals boasted that every family in the town has at least a set of&nbsp;twins!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/igbo ora.jpg" alt="igbo ora" width="307" height="236" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sarki Muhammad Kanta, the Great ruler of Kebbi, was the only ruler who resisted control by Songhai, West Africa&rsquo;s greatest empire at that time. He founded and ruled the Hausa city-state of Kebbi around 1600 A.D and built Surame, its capital, a planned city which was almost impossible to penetrate during the war. In fact UNESCO describes Surame as &ldquo;one of the wonders of human history, creativity and ingenuity&rdquo;, and probably the most massive stone-walled constructions in West Africa. He is listed in Robin Walker&rsquo;s 50 Greatest Africans.</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/map.kebbi1_.gif" alt="kebbi" width="281" height="293" /></p>\r\n<p>Africa&rsquo;s oldest known boat; <strong><em>The Dufuna canoe</em></strong>, was discovered in <strong><em>Dufuna village, Yobe state</em></strong>, by a Fulani Herdsman in <strong><em>May 1987</em></strong>, while he dug a well. Various radio-carbon tests conducted in laboratories of reputable universities in Europe and America indicated that the canoe is over 8,000 years old, thus making it the oldest in Africa and 3rd oldest in the world. The discovery of the canoe has completely changed accepted theories of the history and sophistication of marine technology in Africa.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/dufuna canoe.jpg" alt="canoe" width="440" height="219" />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<img src="../media/multimedia/dufuna canoe 1.jpg" alt="canoe1" width="404" height="215" /></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Sungbo&rsquo;s Eredo,</em></strong> a 160 km rampart equipped with guard houses and moats, is reputed to be the largest single pre-colonial monument (or ancient fortification) in Africa. It is located in present-day Ijebu-Ode, Ogun State. When it was built a millennium ago, it required more earth to be moved during construction than that which completed the building of Great Pyramid of Giza (one of the Seven Wonders of The Ancient World). The most astonishing thing is that Eredo was the biggest city in the world (bigger than Rome and Cairo) during the Middle Ages when it was built!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/sungbo eredo.jpg" alt="sungbo" width="355" height="205" />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img src="../media/multimedia/sungbo 1.jpg" alt="sungbo2" width="342" height="205" /></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Sarki Abdullah Burja of Kano</em></strong> (ruled 1438-1452 AD), the 18th ruler of Ancient Kano, created the first Golden Age in Northern Nigeria and ushered in a period of great prosperity. During his reign, Hausa became the biggest indigenous language spoken in Africa after Swahili.</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/sarki burja.jpg" alt="kano" width="334" height="225" /></p>\r\n<p>The <strong><em>Jos Plateau Indigo bird,</em></strong> a small reddish-brown bird, is found nowhere else on the planet but Plateau state, Nigeria.</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/indigo.jpg" alt="indigo" width="335" height="224" /></p>\r\n<p>The <strong><em>Anambra waxbill</em></strong>, a small bird of many beautiful colours, is found only in Southern Nigeria and nowhere else on earth.</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/waxbill bird 1.jpg" alt="wax" width="309" height="247" />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img src="../media/multimedia/waxbill.png" alt="wax1" width="349" height="246" />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<img src="../media/multimedia/Benin_Anambra_Waxbill_1.jpg" alt="wasx" width="306" height="246" /></p>\r\n<p>The Niger Delta (which is the second largest delta on the planet), has the highest concentration of monotypic fish families in the world, and is also home to sixty percent (60%) of Nigeria&rsquo;s mangrove forests.</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/niger-delta-mangrove-swamp1.jpg" alt="NIG DEL" width="312" height="216" /></p>\r\n<p>You should know too that Nigeria&rsquo;s mangrove forests are the largest in Africa and third largest on earth.</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/mangrove 2.png" alt="ma" width="316" height="212" />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<img src="../media/multimedia/mangrove2.jpg" alt="man1" width="349" height="213" />&nbsp; &nbsp;<img src="../media/multimedia/Mangroves_1.jpg" alt="man 2" width="308" height="211" /></p>\r\n<p>According to the World Resources Institute, Nigeria is home to 4,715 different types of plant species, and over 550 species of breeding birds and mammals, making it one of the most ecologically vibrant places of the plane</p>\r\n<p>And finally, Ile-Ife, in present day State of Osun, was paved as early as 1000AD, with decorations that originated from Ancient America suggesting there might have been contact between the Yorubas and the Ancient Americans half a millennium before Columbus &lsquo;discovered&rsquo; America.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;<img src="../media/multimedia/osun.jpg" alt="osu" width="318" height="286" /></p>', '23, January 2014 04:18:32', '09, July 2014 11:43:42', 'Thu, 23 Jan 2014 04:27:25 +0100', 1125, 73, 0, '13-SHOCKING-FACTS-ABOUT-NIGERIA.', 'no', 'no', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, 'inactive');
INSERT INTO `blogentries` (`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)VALUES( 1, 1, 'normal', 'FUNNY BEHAVIORS IN NIGERIA', '<p>Fellow Nigerians,</p>\r\n<p>Is this how arrests are done?&nbsp;Is there any guideline regarding the arrest of any citizen of this country?</p>\r\n<p>Why do we do things this way? Is this also traceable to bad governance or we just don''t care for one another?</p>\r\n<p>Please share your opinion.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you</p>', '<p><img src="../media/multimedia/Imagine this.jpg" alt="Imagine this" width="554" height="457" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Fellow Nigerians,</p>\r\n<p>Is this how arrests are done? Is there any guideline regarding the arrest of any citizen of this country?</p>\r\n<p>Why do we do things this way? Is this also traceable to bad governance or we just don''t care for one another?</p>\r\n<p>Please share your opinion.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you</p>', '22, January 2014 09:30:29', '09, July 2014 12:03:10', 'Wed, 09 Jul 2014 12:03:10 +0100', 374, 44, 0, 'FUNNY-BEHAVIORS-IN-NIGERIA', 'no', 'no', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, 'inactive');
INSERT INTO `blogentries` (`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)VALUES( 1, 1, 'normal', 'BACKWARD INVESTMENT!', '<p>Nnamdi is 38 years old. A young active very hardworking man,&nbsp;a&nbsp;senior manager in a leading insurance company in Lagos. He&rsquo;s been working very hard right after school about 15 years ago to attain his current career status. He&rsquo;s married with 3 children; he lives at Isolo, a suburb in Lagos.</p>\r\n<p>Nnamdi is currently in distress, the rent of his 3 bedroom apartment is due and he must also pay the school fees of his three children this same week if not, they will not be allowed into school next week.</p>\r\n<p>His car too has engine problems and he needs to buy a new engine, his wife also has just been evicted from the corner shop where she sells fabrics, as she couldn&rsquo;t pay the rent for the last sixteen months.</p>\r\n<p>Though Nnamdi works with a good company and earns a relatively good salary, he&rsquo;s unstable financially due to high bills and financial obligations.</p>', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Nnamdi is 38 years old. A young active very hardworking man, a&nbsp;senior manager in a leading insurance company in Lagos. He&rsquo;s been working very hard right after school about 15 years ago to attain his current career status. He&rsquo;s married with 3 children; he lives at Isolo, a suburb in Lagos.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Nnamdi is currently in distress, the rent of his 3 bedroom apartment is due and he must also pay the school fees of his three children this same week if not, they will not be allowed into school next week.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">His car too has engine problems and he needs to buy a new engine, his wife also has just been evicted from the corner shop where she sells fabrics, as she couldn&rsquo;t pay the rent for the last sixteen months.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Though Nnamdi works with a good company and earns a relatively good salary, he&rsquo;s unstable financially due to high bills and financial obligations.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">His cost of living is perpetually on the increase; feeding, transportation, clothing, accommodation and school fees have been growing at a much faster rate than his salary.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Even now apart from his own 3 kids, he also houses two younger siblings and sponsors their university education at LASU. Nnamdi is the first son of his parents.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Nnamdi today is sad and very unhappy, he just got a letter again from his father living in the village and the content is most distressing as it appears, his father is cursing him for neglecting them in their old age a critical time of need.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">His father believes they&rsquo;ve invested so much in training him and making him a big man and Nnamdi is denying them the right to reap enough fruit from their investment in him.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Nnamdi&rsquo;s father is asking him to send home as a matter of urgency about 250,000 naira to fix a part of the compound fence that has collapsed, buy his mother&rsquo;s blood pressure drugs and settle the lawyer helping with a land dispute matter in the village.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Nnamdi has less than 80,000 naira in his account today. What can he do? What should he do? Steal from his company, take bribe or initiate a fraud? By hook or by crook? Pressure, unnecessary pressure; so sad.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">One of the greatest challenges facing the productive generation in Nigeria today is what I call the backward investment of value.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Many young people today are working very hard and struggling to make ends meet. Unfortunately, they carry a weak conscience tied to a tradition of taking full responsibility for their&nbsp;parents and relatives at old age.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Instead of investing into the future to create a future of financial security and sufficiency for ourselves and our children, we invest more into an exiting generation; a generation leaving the scene that really ought to have made provisions for their future and old age but failed!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">They now transfer the consequence and liability of their failure on their children.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">This trend unfortunately is a major snag on the ability of Nigerians to create and grow wealth.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">A typical Nigeria youth today is working so hard to cater for himself, his children and his parents and relatives.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">An average Nigerian youth is expected to carry the responsibility of three generations at the same time; a very tough call. Since he cannot adequately make provision for himself, his children and secure the future, at old age, he would also expect his children to cater for him and his grand children too - another 3 generations.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">I dare say with this trend our nation may struggle to experience true and rapid wealth creation, sustenance and transfer.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Every wealth created by each generation is squandered by three generations. With this trend, the possibility of adequate wealth creation is unlikely. We will inevitably continue to blame the government and accuse government institutions and agencies for even our own responsibilities.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Every great and thriving economy is driven mostly by the private sector, the government only lends necessary support, in a case where the people expect the government to do everything, there&rsquo;s stagnation and poverty.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">A successful career life is such that can transfer wealth to the next generation, not take wealth from the next generation.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">It is expected that every person should start career by going to school first, next become an employee, next you become self employed, next you become a business owner, then you become an investor then lastly a philanthropist.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In a nation where this orientation is lacking, poverty and stagnation is assured.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Many people today who ought to have become business owners are still in paid employment because they lack financial intelligence and money management capacities. As the money comes, it goes without any plan for investment. Many employees who have worked for 15 to 20 years today may begin to beg within six months of losing their jobs.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">They have no investments and money discipline. They&rsquo;ve wasted all the salaries earned over the years in emotional and sentimental expenditure. Today they have nothing in investment and reserve.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Take a moment to calculate all your income since your career began, how much has truly passed through your hands? What do you have to show for all that money today? Think about it.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Many employees today can&rsquo;t afford to resign, move on and create room for fresh graduates and subordinates to take over their positions, they lack the capital and financial security needed to employ themselves; that&rsquo;s part of our unemployment problems in Nigeria - sit tight employees.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Your children should not be your financial security for the future, if this is your thinking you&rsquo;re part of the problem of Nigeria. It is expected that a good man should leave an inheritance for even his children&rsquo;s children, not eat the inheritance of his children&rsquo;s children!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Start thinking investment today. Learn how to make more money by making your money work for you. Get investment education. Even from that so called small salary, you can put something aside to secure your future!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">You don&rsquo;t need every new shoe, clothing, bag, jewellery, car, suit, and phone, you really may not need a new laptop, electronics and party, must you go on that vacation this year; must you compete with people? Why impress or oppress anybody?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Think of your future today, because truly, it&rsquo;s all about you.</p>', '22, January 2014 09:52:48', '09, July 2014 11:56:57', 'Wed, 09 Jul 2014 11:56:57 +0100', 406, 47, 0, 'BACKWARD-INVESTMENT', 'no', 'no', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, 'inactive');
INSERT INTO `blogentries` (`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)VALUES( 1, 1, 'normal', 'WHAT IS CHRISTIANITY?', '<p>There is a widespread belief that Christianity is a religion! Religion is the effort and attempt by mankind to seek God and establish a relationship with God. Hence, with religion there are several types, beliefs, procedures and means put in place by mankind to reach God. A religious person thus believes all religions have the capacity to reach God and maintain a good relationship with Him.</p>\r\n<p>All religions also believe in the purity and righteousness of God, hence, they all believe reaching God and maintaining a good relationship with him is through morals, keeping rules and regulations, being upright and doing the right thing and generally upholding the law of good conscience.</p>\r\n<p>Mankind has over time developed this concept called religion due to an innate conviction and natural instinct that there is a supreme being somewhere, bigger and more powerful than man who rules and controls the affairs of this world; the whole creation and nature. For man to therefore feel safe, secure, happy and protected, he must seek the protection, goodwill and kindness of this Supreme Being, hence religion became man&rsquo;s answer.</p>', '<p style="text-align: justify;">There is a widespread belief that Christianity is a religion! Religion is the effort and attempt by mankind to seek God and establish a relationship with God. Hence, with religion there are several types, beliefs, procedures and means put in place by mankind to reach God. A religious person thus believes all religions have the capacity to reach God and maintain a good relationship with Him.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">All religions also believe in the purity and righteousness of God, hence, they all believe reaching God and maintaining a good relationship with him is through morals, keeping rules and regulations, being upright and doing the right thing and generally upholding the law of good conscience.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Mankind has over time developed this concept called religion due to an innate conviction and natural instinct that there is a supreme being somewhere, bigger and more powerful than man who rules and controls the affairs of this world; the whole creation and nature. For man to therefore feel safe, secure, happy and protected, he must seek the protection, goodwill and kindness of this Supreme Being, hence religion became man&rsquo;s answer.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">But Christianity is different in meaning, purpose, context and source. While religion is man&rsquo;s attempt to reach out to God, Christianity is God&rsquo;s plan, strategy and purpose in reaching out to man.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Man was created by God in the beginning of time because God wanted a type of Him to exist for friendship and fellowship, hence in Genesis chapter 1 vs. 26, God made man not just in <strong>His</strong> <strong>image</strong> but also in <strong>His likeness</strong> &ndash; looking like God and being like God. And just as God rules in the Heavens he gave man a territory called earth to rule over hence he gave man the power and authority and commandment saying be fruitful, multiply, subdue, have dominion and replenish &ndash; the same five ruler-ship traits of God. (As demonstrated in creation)</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">But man, through deception by the serpent, the wicked one, Lucifer; betrayed a trust, a friendship and a relationship with God and lost his Godlike nature died just like God warned him and man became an ordinary beast. (Genesis:3) His intelligence and ability to exist for ever remained intact though, but his God-like nature died hence, he could not relate with God anymore or relate in God&rsquo;s realm because through death in his spirit man he lost access to his godly realm. (NB: death is not a termination of existence but loss of access to a realm of life or another, mankind has an eternal nature, ability to exist forever)</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">God by his love for mankind now put in place a plan to restore man to his original position as a god.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">By the supernatural law that governs every existing realm and kingdom, blood is the price for sin (Romans 6:23, Hebrews 9:22), so God through his love for mankind decided to restore mankind to his original position as a god by paying the price so that man can continue to be like God on earth.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">God by nature exists as three forms in one (Father, Son, Holy Ghost) just like He created man too to exist as three forms in one (body, soul and spirit) remember we&rsquo;re in his likeness.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">I&rsquo;m sure if you&rsquo;re familiar with witchcraft, you&rsquo;ll know they possess the ability to separate their bodies from their spirits when going for their spiritual engagements. The body is at home, probably asleep but the spirit is in a meeting in a different location and realm.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">If ordinary witches can do this then it shouldn&rsquo;t be a wonder that God the Father also being in heaven sent God the son; the second person of the trinity to the earth realm in form of His son Jesus Christ to pay for the sins of man with his pure blood; void of carnal influence; a birth absolutely delivered by God&rsquo;s spoken word unto Mary just as he spoke Adam into existence in Genesis 1:27. Even Mary&rsquo;s blood didn&rsquo;t mix with that of Jesus as medical science has proven the blood of mothers and babies don&rsquo;t mix during gestation or delivery.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">So God came as Jesus, shed His blood, paid the price and restored mankind to the original state of being a god; godliness through faith and believe in His sacrifice!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Christianity is hence, a state of spiritual restoration to that original condition of being a god, achieved through bloodshed by Jesus who repurchase the status and recovered the authority and power for man.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">This is your experience when you believe and accept the truth that God died as Jesus and paid for the sins of mankind including yours. (The existence of Jesus was not terminated at the cross, he only secured a passage through death to different realms of life to recover power, authority and dominion for mankind from the enemy in all those realms as death is not a termination of existence but a translation from one realm of life to another)</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;Once you accept and confess this truth, your spirit that has lost its godlike nature and has become dead (loss of ability to connect with God&rsquo;s realm) immediately receives <em>spiritual signals</em>; the life of God. A reconnection is established and you become a god again &ndash; re-empowered to be fruitful, to multiply, to subdue, to have dominion and to replenish the earth!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">So Christianity is God&rsquo;s strategy and provision to reconnect mankind to Himself, his kingdom and Spiritual network. This makes Christianity different and more authentic than any other religion. It has its origin in God not mankind.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Although over the years due to lack of understanding and complete revelation of this truth, many preachers have diminished Christianity to a mere religion advocating it&rsquo;s about morality, rules and regulations, obeying the law, dos and don&rsquo;ts. This is absolutely incorrect. It&rsquo;s about the life of God in your spirit man. It&rsquo;s about the god nature in your spirit.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">All religions are powerless against the forces of the wicked one, the devil, Satan. Infact many religions ignorantly worship the devil and his high powered agents. And the devil, through religion will want you to believe doing good and being moral is the way to be reconnected to god and go to heaven! He&rsquo;ll make you think your religion is unto the real God. The devil doesn&rsquo;t mind you doing good and being moral, infact he is happy if you think by doing good you are right with God.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Whether you do good or not, obey the law or not, it doesn&rsquo;t matter to Satan as long &nbsp;as your spirit is yet to receive the life of god through confessing and accepting Jesus Christ and you eventually go to Hell. All he is after is to ensure you go to Hell because as a mere man you cannot get to paradise or heaven; only gods are allowed in there!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Christianity is NOT a religion; it is all about having the Godlike nature in your spirit by confessing Jesus Christ as your Lord and personal Saviour. This confession, this belief is what it means to be Born Again! The rebirth of your god nature! Hallelujah! Accept Jesus today and receive back your godlike nature to escape Hell! God bless you.</p>', '22, January 2014 10:07:34', '', '', 1184, 52, 0, 'WHAT-IS-CHRISTIANITY', 'no', 'no', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, 'active');
INSERT INTO `blogentries` (`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)VALUES( 2, 1, 'normal', 'TODAY ON FRANKLY SPEAKING - THE PURPOSE OF BRANDING', '<p>With the rapid improvement and sophistication in technology, production processes have become a lot more automated. Manual handling in production of goods and service delivery continues to reduce as more advanced computerization empowers many production processes to do things unaided.</p>\r\n<p>Many production machines and lines continue to churn out standard quality products, meeting the specifics, with extremely minimal defects as almost every aspect of the process has been programmed to deliver perfectly. All the engineer needs to do is just program the machines and monitor the process to deliver. The world has come that advanced.</p>\r\n<p>Be it food processing, aviation, automobile, FMCGs, telecoms, office machines, home appliances and equipment, courier and logistics production and service sectors, there are extremely intelligent machines created and well programmed to deliver, superior and standard products and services at much faster rates.</p>', '<p>With the rapid improvement and sophistication in technology, production processes have become a lot more automated. Manual handling in production of goods and service delivery continues to reduce as more advanced computerization empowers many production processes to do things unaided.</p>\r\n<p>Many production machines and lines continue to churn out standard quality products, meeting the specifics, with extremely minimal defects as almost every aspect of the process has been programmed to deliver perfectly. All the engineer needs to do is just program the machines and monitor the process to deliver. The world has come that advanced.</p>\r\n<p>Be it food processing, aviation, automobile, FMCGs, telecoms, office machines, home appliances and equipment, courier and logistics production and service sectors, there are extremely intelligent machines created and well programmed to deliver, superior and standard products and services at much faster rates.</p>\r\n<p>The marvel adjoined to this innovation in manufacturing and production is the speed. What may require a hundred men to churn out in 30 days manually hitherto can be delivered by just one automated machine in 30 minutes. Hence, manufactures are able to produce more and deliver more efficiently in shorter time spans and periods.</p>\r\n<p>As exciting as this may sound, there are consequences attached to this rate of output. Of course the reason for production is consumption. Products are manufactured for consumers to purchase and consume. Though the quality and speed of production has been enhanced tremendously over time, the volume and speed of consumption however has not been able to match or equate production. Consumers don&rsquo;t consume at the same rate producers produce.</p>\r\n<p>Two basic factors I&rsquo;d like to consider, responsible for this are nature and purchasing power. I will not drink 20 bottles of soft drinks at once because the bottling company can now produce one thousand bottles per minute. Even if I want to I can&rsquo;t because it is naturally impossible.</p>\r\n<p>Similarly, I cannot buy 100 brand new cars at the same time because the manufacturers now have the capacity to produce 1000 cars in 5 hours. This is simply because I don&rsquo;t need that number of cars and I can&rsquo;t afford that number of cars. Even if I could afford, it doesn&rsquo;t make sense buying 100 of the same type of car.</p>\r\n<p>The immediate option for manufacturers hence is seeking new markets; new buyers and developing them, but most companies avoid venturing first because of the high cost of virgin market penetration, they&rsquo;ll rather compete in already developed and growing markets.</p>\r\n<p>Hence the improvement and speed in production technology has its own attended challenges.</p>\r\n<p>Besides the fact that product sales; that is offtake or purchases by consumers is far below the quantity manufacturers can produce per occasion nowadays, competitors are also producing as fast and as much products and selling to the same consumers hence, the ability to even sell most of what is produced by a manufacturer is made more difficult by the presence and activities of competitors also talking and selling to the same people in the same market. What&rsquo;s more, competitors may even be able to produce superior quantity and sell at a lower price if they get their value chain process management right and manage it more efficiently.</p>\r\n<p>This situation is inevitably the purpose and what gave rise to branding. Branding is basically the science of differentiating your product from that of competitors by making it recognizable and preferred among similar options.</p>\r\n<p>Branding is driven by the need to create recognition and a relationship with potential consumers; nurture this relationship and bond with the consumer to drive loyalty by fulfilling the promise made to the consumer by the brand.</p>\r\n<p>Branding is essentially in place to make the product the preferred amongst several options available to the customer. This can only be achieved if the brand lives up to its promise.</p>\r\n<p>My dear friends, branding is not just creating recognition for your product, recognition does not sell a product, fulfilling the brand promise is actually what sells the product.</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s really unfortunate nowadays to hear even experts think exciting product identity is what sells a product.</p>\r\n<p>For most establishments, their understanding of the branding concept stops at just the differentiation level. You&rsquo;ll hear people say branding is giving a product a name or an identity via recognizable elements like logo, colors and packaging.</p>\r\n<p>My dear friends, may I announce to you this morning that differentiation is a dangerous venture for a bad product or a brand that can&rsquo;t live up to its promise.</p>\r\n<p>Differentiation is not synonymous to branding. Being different offers the privilege of identification or recognition. When you&rsquo;re different as a product on a shelf or otherwise, I recognize you.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;No matter how lovely and fantastic and beautiful your differentiation is and no matter how poor and inferior the differentiation of your competition is, all differentiation offers me is the ability to recognize your brand and at best be drawn to it.</p>\r\n<p>True branding however is absolutely about the character of the product, my experience with the product and its ability to meet or match my expectations by fulfilling its promise to meet this need the way I expect it to.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;No matter the beauty of your logo, the colors of your envelopes and letter heads, the appearance and good looks of your business premises and employees, and even the excitement of your commercials, if my experience with your offering is disappointing, what your differentiation will do is to help me recognize and avoid your product the next time I go shopping for a product in your category.</p>\r\n<p>The character of your brand will help me form an opinion about it after an experience with your brand. When I try and it&rsquo;s good then I love and prefer it, when I get attracted by packaging and I try and it&rsquo;s bad, then I permanently avoid it.</p>\r\n<p>Differentiation empowers the customer to recognize you so as to either buy you or avoid you. Differentiation is not branding, differentiation is recognition, branding is an experience.</p>\r\n<p>Brand promise is the solution your product carries or the need its meant to satisfy, brand character however is the way and manner this need is satisfied. Brand promise to an extent is generic, all similar products will ultimately make the same promise in different ways, but the experience is what makes the difference, the experience of how well, how efficiently and how excitingly this promise is delivered.</p>\r\n<p>The experience in effect is what forms the opinion of the customer and determines if the customer would be back or will go to competition seeking the same promise but with a superior delivery experience.</p>\r\n<p>Dear friends, business success and profitability this year will be predicated on not just the beauty and class of your brand differentiation or even presentation, your ability to deliver the promise indeed in more superior and affordable ways than competition is the master key to market share expansion and revenue generation.</p>\r\n<p>Much like you my friend, your ability to deliver on your role, tasks and responsibility would go a long way in determining your empowerment, promotion and reward in this new season.</p>\r\n<p>This is beyond your nice suits, ties, skirts, shoes, hair, make up and good looks, it&rsquo;s beyond the ability to speak well and confidently, in fact it goes beyond charisma&nbsp; and popularity. At the end of the period, it is a matter of your objectives and appraisal. Were you able to deliver your objectives for the year? How well did you deliver these objectives; poorly, as expected, or exceeding expectations? Would your delivery style be referenced as excellent?</p>\r\n<p>Do not be deceived, no matter how well differentiated you are or a product is, reward and acceptability is absolutely tied to the ability to meet needs, satisfy needs in the most exciting and affordable manner than competition.</p>\r\n<p>Branding is purely the ability to be different and better than competition, it&rsquo;s not just for recognition and identification; it&rsquo;s for the product promise, product character and consumer experience. Dear friends, brand yourself right!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Enjoy your day.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>CONNECT WITH US ON SOCIAL MEDIA!</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Twitter:</strong>&nbsp;@franklyafolabi or&nbsp;<strong>Click</strong>&nbsp;<a href="http://www.twitter.com/franklyafolabi">http://www.twitter.com/franklyafolabi</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>Facebook fan page</strong>:&nbsp;<strong>Click to Like</strong>&nbsp;<a href="http://www.facebook.com/franklyspeakingwithmuyiwaafolabi">http://www.facebook.com/franklyspeakingwithmuyiwaafolabi</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>Google Plus</strong>: Muyiwa Afolabi</p>', '23, January 2014 05:29:36', '24, January 2014 02:22:53', 'Thu, 23 Jan 2014 12:50:32 +0100', 516, 74, 0, 'TODAY-ON-FRANKLY-SPEAKING--THE-PURPOSE-OF-BRANDING', 'no', 'no', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, 'active');
INSERT INTO `blogentries` (`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)VALUES( 1, 1, 'normal', '2014 FASHION TRENDS', '<p>Dear Friends,</p>\r\n<p>''Looking good is good business!'' they say, check out these lovely fashion items designed to stand you out and make you look adorable in 2014.</p>\r\n<p>They are nice!<img src="../scripts/js/tinymce/plugins/emoticons/img/smiley-laughing.gif" alt="" /></p>', '<p>Dear Friends,</p>\r\n<p>''Looking good is&nbsp;good business!'' they say, check out these lovely fashion items designed to stand you out and make you look adorable&nbsp;in 2014.</p>\r\n<p>They are nice!<img src="../scripts/js/tinymce/plugins/emoticons/img/smiley-laughing.gif" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/bag.jpg" alt="bag" width="302" height="342" /></p>\r\n<p>Raspberry Envelope Tote bag by NEXT</p>\r\n<p>Price:$55</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/Gucci khaki pants.jpg" alt="gucci" width="278" height="247" /></p>\r\n<p>Gucci mens slim cotton trousers, Khaki by Gucci</p>\r\n<p>Price:$169.99</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/jimmy choo black.jpg" alt="jimmy" width="281" height="281" /></p>\r\n<p>Jimmy choo Ravish</p>\r\n<p>These shoes are dazzling and a choice for evening events.</p>\r\n<p>Price:$850</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/jimmy choo male black.jpg" alt="jimmy" width="329" height="203" /></p>\r\n<p>Jimmy choo</p>\r\n<p>White sole mocasine with beige lace.&nbsp;Black</p>\r\n<p>Price:$525</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/shirt.jpg" alt="shirt" width="301" height="384" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Calvin klein lavender coloured slim fit shirt</p>\r\n<p>Price:$89.50</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/waist coat.jpg" alt="waist" width="231" height="295" /></p>\r\n<p>Calvin klein black formal vest</p>\r\n<p>Price:$79.99</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/Gaofan wallets.jpg" alt="wallets" width="304" height="302" /></p>\r\n<p>Gaofan leather brown wallet for ladies&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Price:$22.99</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/shoe.jpg" alt="shouy" width="260" height="390" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NEXT: Navy blue placement lace peep toe courts, made in a soft fabric sole and high heel.</p>\r\n<p>Price:$49</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/watch.jpg" alt="watch" width="400" height="600" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NEXT&rsquo;s wristwatch for female with silver stunnings</p>\r\n<p>Price:$50</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/gucci perfume.jpg" alt="perf" width="377" height="377" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Gucci guilty perfume</p>\r\n<p>Price:$55</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '23, January 2014 07:28:17', '23, January 2014 07:37:08', 'Thu, 23 Jan 2014 07:37:08 +0100', 1541, 75, 0, '2014-FASHION-TRENDS', 'no', 'no', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, 'active');
INSERT INTO `blogentries` (`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)VALUES( 2, 1, 'normal', 'TOUCH OF GOLD', '<p>18-carat-gold HTC One-crafted specially to mark the 2013 MOBO Awards. There were only five in existence, and at such a premium price (&pound;2,750), it&nbsp;was the most expensive phone HTC had ever produced.&nbsp;HTC liked the design so much it''s now available as a colour option. So it''s not pure&nbsp;gold but nice enough to sit alongside the silver, red and black models.</p>', '<p><img src="../media/multimedia/htc.jpg" alt="case" width="400" height="391" />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<img src="../media/multimedia/htc2.jpg" alt="htc" width="427" height="312" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;18-carat-gold HTC One-crafted specially to mark the 2013 MOBO Awards. There were only five in existence, and at such a premium price (&pound;2,750), it&nbsp;was the most expensive phone HTC had ever produced.&nbsp;HTC liked the design so much it''s now available as a colour option. So it''s not pure&nbsp;gold but nice enough to sit alongside the silver, red and black models.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/ear phones.jpg" alt="ear" width="409" height="307" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Piano Forte X-VIII Series earphones</strong></p>\r\n<p>The mere mention of gold and headphones may well fill you with scepticism. Japanese high-end audio specialists ''Final Audio Design'' came up with some headgear that perfectly marries the two. Each speaker is powered by larger than average driver units while metallic earbuds deliver the sound. Together this makes for a wide, concert hall-like soundstage.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '23, January 2014 09:57:26', '24, January 2014 02:21:44', 'Thu, 23 Jan 2014 09:58:39 +0100', 1083, 76, 0, 'TOUCH-OF-GOLD', 'no', 'no', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, 'active');
INSERT INTO `blogentries` (`blogtypeid`, `blogcatid`, `blogentrytype`, `title`, `introparagraph`, `blogpost`, `entrydate`, `modifydate`, `feeddate`, `views`, `coverphoto`, `coverphotoset`, `pagename`, `commentsonoff`, `featuredpost`,  `postperiod`, `date`, `tags`, `seometakeywords`, `posterid`, `status`)VALUES( 1, 1, 'normal', 'IGHO SANOMI; AFRICA''S YOUNGEST BILLIONAIRE', '<p>Igho Charles Sanomi II was born in 1975 in Agbor Delta State, Nigeria, the fifth child (and first son) of a devout Catholic family. His father, the late Dickens Oghenereumu Patrick Sanomi hailed from Delta State Nigeria and was a retired Assistant Inspector General of the Nigerian Police. Mr Sanomi&rsquo;s mother, Mabel Iyabo Sanomi holds a Royal title of Yeye Jemo of Isotun Ijesha Kingdom in Osun State. She was a renowned nurse and medical entrepreneur from Osun State in South Western Nigeria.</p>', '<p>Igho Charles Sanomi II was born in 1975 in Agbor Delta State, Nigeria, the fifth child (and first son) of a devout Catholic family. His father, the late Dickens Oghenereumu Patrick Sanomi hailed from Delta State Nigeria and was a retired Assistant Inspector General of the Nigerian Police. Mr Sanomi&rsquo;s mother, Mabel Iyabo Sanomi holds a Royal title of Yeye Jemo of Isotun Ijesha Kingdom in Osun State. She was a renowned nurse and medical entrepreneur from Osun State in South Western Nigeria.</p>\r\n<p>Mr Sanomi entered the world of business shortly after completing his Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Geology and Mining at the University of Jos in Northern Nigeria. He rose quickly to the position of Executive Director with Sarian Oil and Cosmos Oil AG, an international Oil Trading Company with its core activities in West Africa. &nbsp;During his time in this role he single handedly developed the company&rsquo;s trading operations by negotiating the export and delivery of fuel oils from West Africa to the United States Gulf Coast. He also developed a strategic alliance with a major international oil trading group based in Zug, Switzerland. This partnership oversaw the import and export of millions of tons of refined petroleum products to and from the West African coast.</p>\r\n<p>Mr Sanomi is the CEO of the Taleveras Group he founded in 2004. Mr Sanomi is also Chairman of the Dickens Sanomi Foundation board of Trustees, Dickens Sanomi Foundation is a non-profit charitable organisation which he founded in memory of his late father. He also sits as Chairman and Co- Chairman of various companies Board of Directors, which he founded or co-founded. These companies activities span from Telecom to Shipping, Aviation and Real Estate Investments worldwide.</p>\r\n<p>His vision and drive has turned the Taleveras Group into an internationally recognized energy and power conglomerate, with offices in London, Geneva, Cape Town, Dubai, Ivory Coast, Abuja and Lagos. Visit the <a href="http://www.ighosanomi.com/business/">business</a> page to read more about Mr Sanomi&rsquo;s current business activities.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src="../media/multimedia/private jet.jpg" alt="" width="415" height="277" /></p>\r\n<p>IGHO SANOMI&rsquo;S PRIVATE JET</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Igho Charles Sanomi II is the young, dynamic founder and Chief Executive Officer of the Taleveras Group, an internationally recognized energy and power conglomerate with offices in London, Geneva, Cape Town, Dubai, the Ivory Coast, Abuja and Lagos. He also acts as Chairman or Co-chair on the boards of companies with interests as diverse as construction, telecommunications, shipping, aviation and real estate.</p>\r\n<p>In his role as CEO, Mr Sanomi ensures that the Taleveras Group is always focused on activities that deliver social and economic benefits to the regions where they take place. Thanks to his strong leadership the Taleveras Group shares Mr Sanomi&rsquo;s personal ideals of ethical conduct, humanitarianism and environmental sustainability.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '24, January 2014 09:31:08', '', '', 38653, 77, 0, 'IGHO-SANOMI-AFRICAS-YOUNGEST-BILLIONAIRE', 'no', 'no', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, 'active');
